<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Chiapas Bulletin No. 23 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2101140794 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2101140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bulletin No. 23 issued by the Mexican National Defense </F>
Secretariat in Mexico City on 20 January; from the "24 Hours 
Newscast"] 
  [Text] As the process of normalization of the situation in 
highland, jungle, and border municipalities in Chiapas State 
progresses, most Army troops remain confined to quarters near 
San Cristobal de las Casas, Oxchuc, Ocosingo, Altamirano, and 
Las Margaritas, apart from Army troops stationed at the military 
installations of Rancho Nuevo and Comitan. This situation has 
permitted civilian authorities to carry out their normal 
activities and direct their efforts to provide humanitarian 
assistance to the population. 
  Soldiers continue to assist the civilian population by 
transporting and distributing supplies, blankets, and medicine 
to the affected towns. These actions are also being carried out 
freely by different social groups, the Red Cross, and 
nongovernment organizations. 
  The Army will continue to participate in these humanitarian 
tasks and will assist civil institutions and organizations that 
require its assistance. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

