<H3> <TI>   Salinas Signs Chiapas Tax Exemption Decree </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2101164394 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2101164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The federal government announced new measures to 
contribute to the normalization of the economy in Chiapas and 
overcome the conflict. President Carlos Salinas de Gortari 
issued a decree condoning the payment of income taxes for 
taxpayers in 21 municipalities of Chiapas State between January 
and June 1994. The decree also exempts taxpayers from paying 
property tax if their business address is located in the 
adversely affected region. 

</TEXT>

