<H3> <TI>   OAS Candidate on Reintegrating Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2201042894 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0000 GMT 22 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2201042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Costa Rican Foreign Minister Bernd Niehaus has said 
he will reintegrate Cuba into the OAS if he is elected OAS 
secretary general. In statements to the Colombian radio network 
Radio Cadena Nacional, Niehaus said, regarding OAS Charter 
principles, Cuba is a member of the American continent and 
should be a full member of the OAS. 
  Niehaus expressed confidence about winning the OAS secretary 
general position, and he revealed he anticipates 22 votes in his 
favor. Only 18 votes are required to win. 

