<H3> <TI>   19 Jan Chamber of Deputies Opening Aborted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2001184594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 20 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL2001184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The opening of the Assembly session was aborted when 
only 30 deputies answered the second roll call. Chamber of 
Deputies President Frantz Robert Monde says that all measures 
that can be considered will be taken jointly with the majority 
in order to deal with this attempted boycott. Monde says it is 
shameful that parliamentarians who regularly receive their 
salaries are refusing to attend the sessions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

