<F P=100> Bermuda </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   People's Congress Establishes New Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2101161294 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1400 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2101161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The people's Congress for National Salvation 
concluded its work on 20 January with the adoption of a 
resolution establishing a three-member government of public 
security. At the conclusion of three days of debates and works 
in small committees, gathered at the National Theater, about 100 
delegates representing the nine geographic departments of the 
country demanded the formation of this government consisting of 
Notary Public Raoul Kenol; industrialist Charles Plaisimond, and 
Cap-Haitien Court of Appeal Judge Louis Toussaint. 
  This government's mission is to normalize conditions, 
promote 
national reconciliation, and restore the authority of the state. 
  The congress, which was held on the initiative of the Great 
North citizens group, calls for general concerted action and 
condemns the embargo ordered against Haiti. The delegates 
brought their principal voted resolutions to the office of the 
Chamber of Deputies in the hope of enforcement as a matter of 
urgency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-51641 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat015_b_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-015 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

