<H3> <TI>   Formal Acknowledgement Sought </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2101165294 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2101165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Congress for National Salvation decided to 
form a government of public security. The participants have gone 
to the Legislative Palace to meet with the president of the 
National Assembly for formal acknowledgement of this 
three-member government. The following is a recorded report by 
Jean Luckenson. 
  [Begin recording in Creole] A government of public security 
was established on Thursday, 20 January at 1600 as the result of 
a resolution by the Congress for National Salvation, which held 
a conference at the National Theater from 18 to 20 January. It 
was organized by the Great North citizens group. Following a 
series of workshops, three people were chosen to lead this 
government: Raoul Kenol, a lawyer representing the Artibonite 
Department; Charles Plaisimond, an industrialist representing 
the Department of the West; and Louis Toussaint, judge at the 
Court of Appeals in Cap-Haitien. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

