<F P=100> Bermuda </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Hosts Delegates of New Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2101171994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1400 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2101171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The General Command of the Haitian Armed Forces 
advises that it received the members of the office of the 
Haitian people's Congress for National Salvation on 20 January. 
  During this meeting, the delegates informed the General 
Command that representatives of the 41 districts of the Republic 
had voted final resolutions condemning the embargo and its 
effects, and demanding the formation of a government of public 
security. 
  They also informed the military institution that the 
original 
of those resolutions had been entrusted to the Chamber of 
Deputies, but presented a copy of this document to the General 
Command. 
  This information was released in a communique from General 
Headquarters. 

</TEXT>

