<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Denies Owing Debt to Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2001195694 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1700 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2001195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chilean Government has stated that it owes 
nothing to Russian authorities over the renting of ships under 
the Salvador Allende administration. 
  CORFO [Production Development Corporation] Chairman Rene 
Aveliuk said the issue took place in 1973, when the Arauco 
Fishing Company, a CORFO branch which no longer exists, rented 
Russian ships. 
  He said that the Chilean Government knows what to do over a 
Russian Government demand for compensation. 
  [Begin Aveliuk recording, in progress] ... CORFO believes it 
has absolutely nothing to do with them. This is obvious because 
it was an associated enterprise, which is very different from 
CORFO. Everything is over, concluded, and closed. This is what 
we have said and this is what we will continue to say. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

