<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 20 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2101104494 </F>
<F P=103> PY2101104494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Peru monitored through 20 
January. 
  The Spanish Government approved a $40 million loan for Peru 
that will be used to buy Spanish goods and services to implement 
a fiber optic transmission project with the participation of the 
Spanish telecommunications company Alcatel. (Lima EL COMERCIO in 
Spanish 31 Dec 93 p 1) 
  The National Institute of Statistics and Information Science 
on 31 December 1993 reported that 1993's inflation rate was 39.5 
percent, the lowest since 1977. The sectors registering the 
highest increase were: transportation and communications, 54.2 
percent; teaching and cultural services, 46.8 percent; health 
and medical services, 43.7 percent; rental, oil, and 
electricity, 43 percent. The GDP increased 6.8 percent compared 
with 1992. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 1 Jan 94 p 1) 

</TEXT>

