<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guerrilla Attack in Apartado Leaves 29 Dead </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2301140994 Paris AFP in Spanish 1304 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2301140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 23 Jan (AFP) -- Police sources 
have reported that 29 persons died and 11 others were seriously 
wounded in an attack today by the Revolutionary Armed Forces of 
Colombia [FARC] in the downtown area of Apartado, in the banana 
producing area in the northwestern Province of Antioquia. 
  This is the worst carnage so far this year in Antioquia's 
Uraba region, the authorities noted. They explained that 
approximately 20 FARC men armed with rifles and machine guns 
fired indiscriminately on sympathizers of the Hope, Peace, and 
Liberty group composed of former Popular Liberation Army 
guerrillas, who three years ago demobilized and returned to 
civilian life. 
  According to initial investigations by the Antioquia Police, 
the rebels, who wore army and police uniforms, appeared in the 
La Chinita neighborhood, where a party was going on, and opened 
fire. 

</TEXT>

