<H3> <TI>   Military Troops Rescue FARC-Held Doctor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2301221894 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2301221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Diego Fajardo; from the "NTC" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] Military troops rescued this morning Dr. Carlos 
Upegui Zapata from his captors, who were holding him in a hilly 
area between the Municipalities of Viani and Chaguani, 
Cundinamarca. 
  Carlos Upegui Zapata has lived the worst five months of his 
life in these hills. Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia 
[FARC] guerrillas had kept him moving constantly, always in the 
mountains between the Cundinamarca Municipalities of Viani and 
Chaguani. The operation that freed him began at 0550. 
  [Begin recording] [Fajardo] How were you able to rescue the 
doctor alive, considering that he was in, practically speaking, 
a guerrilla hideout? 
  [Unidentified speaker] Due to the way the operation was 
organized and due to the energy and aggressiveness the soldiers 
exhibited. [end recording] 
  One of the guerrillas died in the house in which Upegui was 
hidden; the others fled when they noticed the soldiers' presence. 
  The people of the area say this is an area of working 
peasants and that they did not know anything about the presence 
of guerrillas or kidnapped individuals. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

