<F P=102>  PA1901184794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1901184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Cesar Gaviria has just signed a decree 
whereby he freezes government workers' payroll. That means that 
as of today there will be no new appointments to government 
posts until the electoral process is concluded. The goal is to 
grant the elections honesty. Here is what Planning Director 
Armando Montenegro said: 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Mr. Montenegro, 
why 
was the decision to freeze the government payroll made today? 
  [Montenegro] This is a normal decision during the period 
before the elections to guarantee impartiality. The 
appointments of employees and officials run the risk of 
mid-level officials using them for political reasons. 
  [Reporter] How long will this decision remain in force? 
  [Montenegro] This will remain in force until after the 
elections. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

