<H3> <TI>   Armed Men Kidnap Popayan Municipal Council President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2101140094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2101140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Adolfo Leon Mejia; from the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Indignation prevails among the residents of Popayan 
over the disappearance and kidnapping of Julio Cesar Payan de la 
Roche -- doctor, journalist, and political leader. 
  The first reports indicate the president of Popayan's 
municipal council was intercepted near his farm by several men 
who forced him into a Jeep and took him to an unknown 
destination. 
  [Begin Popayan Mayor Luis Fernando Velasco recording] I hope 
the kidnappers understand they have not attacked Payan the 
doctor. They have actually attacked a whole city, which 
renounces this action and demands his immediate release. [end 
recording] 
  Hundreds of demonstrators from the M-19 Democratic Alliance 
and other movements in the department are currently gathered at 
Caldas Park to protest his kidnapping and to demand that the 
outstanding public leader promptly be released. 
  Dr. Payan was president of the municipal council. He was 
also a journalist who participated in a talk show at Radio 
Super, a local station. He attended to his patients at a 
general clinic located north of this department capital. 
  A complete mystery surrounds the disappearance of Dr. Julio 
Cesar Payan in the city of Popayan. 

</TEXT>

