<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   VAT Protests, Disturbances Break Out in Caracas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901162494 Paris AFP in Spanish 1558 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1901162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 19 Jan (AFP) -- Disturbances broke out at 
noon today in Caracas to protest the value-added tax (VAT), even 
though its implementation at the consumer level was suspended 
until 28 February, reporters at the site of the disturbances 
reported. 
  The disturbances broke out near the Central University of 
Venezuela, where hooded students set fire to a soft drink 
company truck, and in secondary schools and higher education 
centers in central and southwestern Caracas. 

</TEXT>

