<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Committee Created To Continue Budget CPI Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2401200794 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 1500 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2401200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Chamber of Deputies President Inocencio de 
Oliveira today ordered the creation of a control committee to 
continue the work of the Budget CPI [Congressional Investigating 
Committee] and scrutinize those congressmen the CPI report 
recommends be further investigated. This control committee will 
have 30 days to conclude its work, and will be made up of seven 
congressmen. It will be coordinated by the Chamber of Deputies 
vice president, Deputy Fernando Lira, and the rapporteur will be 
Deputy Vital do Rego, comptroller of the lower house. 
  Meanwhile, the final Budget CPI report must be corrected 
before it is delivered to the presidents of the Senate and the 
Chamber of Deputies. [passage omitted] 
  Budget CPI President Senator Jarbas Passarinho spent the 
morning in his house organizing the documents that arrived at 
the last moment at the CPI, and which must be added to the final 
report. One of the documents which arrived during the weekend 
is a report from Sergipe Governor Joao Alves demonstrating that 
his assets are compatible with his income. The document was 
processed by rapporteur Deputy Roberto Magalhaes. 
  Senator Passarinho must hand in the final CPI report to the 
Chamber of Deputies president this afternoon. But this will 
only take place if the Senate data processing service manages to 
print the report with the corrections made by the CPI members 
and the improvised commentaries made by the rapporteur as he 
read the final report. 
  Furthermore, Chamber of Deputies President Inocencio de 
Oliveira said that the Constitution and Justice Committee, which 
must judge the congressmen mentioned in the CPI report, must 
have its composition reorganized before the end of the week. 
Some of the current members of this committee are mentioned in 
the final CPI report, so they must be replaced. 
  [Begin Oliveira recording] The decisions of the Constitution 
and Justice Committee, which is made up of 54 members, are made 
through a vote. I believe that the congressmen mentioned in the 
CPI report must be removed from their posts by their party 
leaders. [end recording] 
  The government will also intensify the investigations on the 
involvement of Executive Branch officials in the budget scandal. 
A special investigative committee presided over by Federal 
Administration Secretary Romildo Canhim will be installed in the 
first week of February. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

