<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Incidents Mark Privatization of Petrochemical Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2501012994 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2200 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2501012994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] There was disorder in downtown Rio de Janeiro 
during the auctioning of Petroquimica Uniao. The privatization 
of the company has been postponed for the third time, and should 
be completed tomorrow. 
  The auction was not concluded because only 64 percent of the 
shares, worth 90 billion real cruzeiros, had been sold. In 
order to transfer the company it is necessary to sell 75 percent 
of the shares. Brokers will bid for the remaining shares 
tomorrow. 
  The auction lasted 11 minutes. The demonstrators, who were 
on the streets and did not get close to the stock market 
building because of security measures, decided to stage a march 
during which they stoned the facades of several banks in 
downtown Rio de Janeiro. A military policeman was wounded in the 
face, and a military police battalion closed the street. 
[passage omitted] 
  The march cut off traffic in Rio Branco Avenue, one of the 
main downtown avenues, and ended in front of the Petrobras 
[Brazilian Petroleum Corporation] building. 
  Two people were reported wounded during the incidents, but 
no 
one was reported arrested. 

</TEXT>

