<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fishing Undersecretariat Abolished, Functions Transferred </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2001001894 Buenos Aires LA NACION in Spanish 19 Jan 94 
Section 2 p 4--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2001001894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA NACION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Argentine Fishing Undersecretariat -- whose 
head, Fernando Gutierrez, tendered his resignation two weeks ago 
-- has been abolished. 
  This decision was made after a two-hour meeting between 
Economy Minister Domingo Cavallo and Felipe Sola, the 
agriculture, livestock, and fishing secretary. This was 
reported by Sola yesterday during a news conference. 
  The fishing functions will be exercised by the agriculture 
secretary, supported by a group of advisers who will not exceed 
the number of advisers already used by Gutierrez. 
  Sola will be supported by Felix Cirio, the under secretary 
for agriculture and livestock production and markets, who will 
replace incumbent Roberto Baltar in the Fishing Directorate, and 
Agrarian Economy Under Secretary Jesus Leguiza, who will 
contribute with statistical data on catches, fleets, and fishing 
economic reviews. Sola said: "This point definitely represents 
a weakness for us." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

