<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2101112994 --FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PY2101112994 </F>
<F P=104>  --FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following ia a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Brazil monitored through 20 
January. 
  According to the Getulio Vargas Foundation, the 1993 
inflation rate measured by the Average General Price Index, 
IGP-M, was 2,567.46 percent, the highest ever in Brazil. The 
December inflation rate was 38.32 percent, 2.17 percentage 
points higher than the 36.15 percent in November. This is the 
highest rate since March 1990, which was a record 81.3 percent. 
(Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 30 Dec 93 
Economic and Business Section p 1) 
  According to the Brazilian Institute of Geography and 
Statistics, the 1993 inflation rate measured by the National 
Consumer Price Index, INPC, was 2,489.11 percent. The Expanded 
Consumer Price Index, IPCA, was 2,474.15 percent. (Rio de 
Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 14 Jan 94 Business and 
Finance Section p 1) 

</TEXT>

