<H3> <TI>   Zimbabwean Secretary Welcomes Robaina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1601035494 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1405 GMT 15 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1601035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Harare, 15 Jan (PL) -- Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina received here today a friendly welcome from 
Stansilus Chigwedere, permanent secretary of the Foreign 
Ministry, who underscored the common interests of the two 
countries. 
  We welcome, Chigwedere said at the air terminal, someone who 
represents a state that has shown its solidarity with Zimbabwe 
since its struggle for independence and with which we share many 
positions. 
  The high-ranking official spoke on behalf of Foreign 
Minister 
Nathan Shamuyarira, who will be abroad until tomorrow. 
  Robaina described as a privilege the visit of the delegation 
he is heading, because it affords the opportunity of a direct 
contact with something that is part of our African history and 
traditions. 
  "We aspire to know each other better, to explain how my 
people live and work, and to exchange mutually beneficial 
experiences," he stated. 
  The Cuban minister will complete a three-day visit during 
the 
third leg of an area tour which started in Ghana and Angola and 
will continue in Zambia and Namibia. 
  The welcoming ceremony was attended by Cuban Ambassador 
Designate Pedro Nunez Mosquera and Charge d'affaires Marcos 
Rodriguez Costa, among other officials. 

</TEXT>

