<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation To Attend Nonaligned Meeting in Jakarta </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2001212894 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1721 GMT 18 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2001212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 18 Jan (PL) -- Cuba will attend an informal 
meeting of the Nonaligned Movement (NOAL) in Jakarta, Indonesia, 
from 9 to 11 February to coordinate positions with 
representatives from 16 countries. 
  A spokesperson for the Foreign Relations Ministry told 
PRENSA 
LATINA that the forum could be considered a preliminary phase 
for the Ministers Conference Summit, which will be held in 
Cairo, Egypt, from 31 May to 3 June. 
  The spokesperson noted that representatives from Egypt, 
Zambia, Algeria, Sri Lanka, Cuba, India, and Zimbabwe -- 
countries that led the movement at different stages -- will be 
among those attending. 
  Delegations from Chipre, Ghana, Colombia, Malaysia, Chile, 
Iran, Saudi Arabia, Syria, and Indonesia, the Movement's current 
president, will also attend in an attempt to outline future 
strategies for the NOAL. The participants could also try to 
decide upon a host for the 11th summit. 

</TEXT>

