<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Endorsements of Gruber as Presidential Candidate </TI></H3>
<H4>   PLA Nominates </H4>
<F P=102> PA2401193694 Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA in Spanish 24 Jan 
94 p 1a </F>

<F P=103> PA2401193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Carlos Vargas] </F>
  [Text] The Authentic Liberal Party [PLA] yesterday 
nominated Mireya Moscoso de Gruber for president, Arnulfo 
Escalona for first vice president, and Jose Teran Sitton for 
second vice president during the party's fourth national 
convention in Chitre, Herrera Province. 
  Only six delegates, including Legislator Hernan Gnaeggi and 
Luis Ramon Fabrega, abstained from voting in favor of the 
presidential ticket proposed by convention leader Joaquin 
Fernando Franco, who chaired the PLA meeting. 
  A total of 221 out of 257 delegates attended the convention, 
which proceeded slowly after starting three hours late due to a 
blackout. Franco said the process was slow "because we took the 
utmost care to avoid having to face another challenge." 
  The convention delegates amended two articles of the party's 
statutes and elected the National Executive Authority with 
chairman Arnulfo Escalona, the members of the National Political 
Authority, and the members of the Honor Court. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

