<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Creates Amnesty, Reconciliation Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2401210894 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2401210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Francisco Trejo; from the "Good Morning From </F>
Mexico" newscast] 
  [Text] President Salinas created during the weekend of 21 
January the Amnesty and Reconciliation Commission, which will 
benefit those involved in the violent actions in Chiapas. Here 
is Francisco Trejo with a report: 
  [Begin Trejo recording] The federal government issued on 22 
January the Amnesty Law, which will benefit all those involved 
in the violent actions in Chiapas from 1 January until 1500 20 
January 1994. The law, which was published in the Official 
Gazette, became effective as of 22 January, and it has four 
permanent articles and two transitory ones. 
  Article One of the text contains the Amnesty Law, which 
favors all those against whom any legal action were or could be 
taken before the federal courts due to crimes associated with 
the violent actions on 1 January 1994. The executive 
established a commission that will coordinate implementation of 
the law. 
  Article Two establishes that those who are either inside or 
outside of the country due to crimes indicated in Article One 
will be able to benefit from the amnesty as long as they release 
hostages and turn in their weapons. 
  In Article Three the amnesty permits the application of the 
law and civil responsibility [responsabilidad civil] of those 
who request it. 
  Those who benefit from the law cannot be in the future 
questioned investigated, arrested, apprehended, or tried in 
accordance with the terms of the current amnesty. The Amnesty 
Law will be published throughout the conflict area in both 
Spanish and the native dialects. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

