<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   PCC Municipal Leader Announces Economic Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2401224894 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2032 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2401224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] (Andres E. Rivero), first secretary of the Communist 
Party of Cuba [PCC] in San Nicolas Municipality, Havana 
Province, has announced that the PCC will pay special attention 
to economic efficiency in all sectors this year, principally in 
the production sector. (Rivero) said that in San Nicolas, like 
everywhere else in Cuba, economic problems are being discussed 
at the work centers and analyses are being conducted on ways to 
reduce subsidies to the management and budgetary systems, while 
producing more with the available raw materials. 
  The PCC municipal leader stressed that the PCC's attention 
in 
the province is focused on increasing cane production by 20,000 
arrobas per caballeria in the 1994-95 harvest. He said they also 
aim to continue the tasks of defense and recovery in 
cattle-raising, as well as the fuel conservation policy. 

</TEXT>

