<H3> <TI>   AALAPSO Sponsors Solidarity Meeting in Havana </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2401224994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2035 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2401224994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A heavily attended and militant ceremony of 
solidarity with Cuba, organized by the executive secretariat of 
AALAPSO [Afro-Asian-Latin America People's Solidarity 
Organization], was held at the international press center's 
Havana location. Support for the Cuban Revolution was expressed 
by numerous representatives of national liberation movements, 
union and cultural organizations, and participants in the Fourth 
Latin American and Caribbean Meeting that begins tomorrow at the 
Convention Center. 
  AALAPSO Secretary General Rene Anillo Capote gave the first 
of the speeches at this ceremony for solidarity with Cuba, which 
was presided over by Jaime Crombet, vice president of the 
National Assembly of the People's Government. This open forum 
for solidarity with Cuba denounced U.S. imperialism's unchanging 
and systematically aggressive policy against our country, and 
the criminal economic and financial blockade. 

</TEXT>

