<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Human Rights Leader Reports Attack on Dissident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2401201894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1840 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2401201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 24 Jan (EFE) -- Elizardo Sanchez Santacruz, 
chairman of the Cuban Commission for Human Rights and National 
Reconciliation (CCDHRN), has charged today that individuals in 
civilian clothes brutally beat group spokesman Rene del Pozo as 
he rode a bicycle in a Havana neighborhood. Sanchez, who stated 
the attack was "carefully planned," told EFE that Rene del Pozo 
was beaten a number of times in the head, abdomen, and back, and 
needed to be treated for bruises at Havana's surgical hospital. 
  According to Sanchez, in the past two weeks, Rolando Pages 
and Elizardo San Pedro, two other activists of the most moderate 
group of internal dissidents, were the target of similar attacks 
"always under strange circumstances," and had to be taken to 
hospitals. In his opinion, these are "repressive and 
intimidatory actions by the Cuban Government's political police 
against peaceful citizens who want to express their disagreement 
with the continuous violations of civil and political rights." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

