<H3> <TI>   Radio Festival Celebrates Remote Transmission Start-ups </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2501002694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2058 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2501002694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Guantanamo radio festival began yesterday in the 
Caujeri Valley with the incorporation of dozens of workers into 
agricultural tasks and the beginning of remote transmissions. 
  The workers from radio stations CMKS, "Radio Trinchera 
Anti-Imperialista," and (CMDX, "La Voz del Toa"), in the 
important area city of Baracoa, will spend several days doing 
work in support of the food program in order to contribute to 
furthering the planting plan of some 25 caballerias of tomatoes. 
  Prior to this, the jury for the event reflected upon and 
analyzed more than 50 works of various kinds. The best programs, 
documentaries, news reports, reportages, and other works from 
among these will win prizes. 
  Assembly brigades are working quickly to install equipment 
in 
the radio studios of the chief municipal towns of Imias and San 
Antonio del Sur. These studios will be inaugurated at the end of 
this month. 

</TEXT>

