<H3> <TI>   Fuel Shortage Reduces School Week to 3 Days </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2401213494 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2401213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beginning this Monday [24 January], many 
congregationist schools in Port-au-Prince have decided to 
operate only three times a week: Mondays, Wednesdays, and 
Fridays. This decision was made by the association of the 
directors of those schools working in Port-au-Prince. This 
decision is a direct consequence of the shortage of fuel and the 
scarcity of oil product in Port-au-Prince. 
  We will later discuss the details of this news item, 
especially with regard to the closing of industries and 
businesses in Port-au- Prince. For instance, the radio stations 
in the capital last week began working on a reduced schedule. 

</TEXT>

