<F P=103> FL2401213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the daily newspaper, LE NOUVELISTE, 
changes have been made within the Haitian Armed Forces. The 
newspaper notes that several transfers were recently effected 
within the Haitian Armed Forces, including changes at the heads 
of two units: the Aviation Corps, in which Colonel Wilson 
Eustache was replaced by Lieutenant-Colonel Serge Bourdeau, who 
has been promoted to the rank of colonel. Second, the Corps of 
Engineers where Lt.-Col. Rodrigue Creve-Coeur, promoted to 
colonel, succeeds Col. Guy Duchemin, who has been pensioned off. 
Col. Wilson Eustache has been allegedly called to the personal 
general staff of the Army commander in chief. 

