<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments Through 25 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2501153694 </F>
<F P=103> PA2501153694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Guatemalan economic developments monitored through 25 
January. Source is cited in parentheses following each item: 
  The Bank of Guatemala president reported that demand for 
foreign currency as of 14 January totalled $35.6 million. He 
added that this fact could be the result of the present 
political uncertainty. The official noted that the exchange rate 
remains relatively stable. The Bank president also reported that 
international monetary reserves have gone from $738 million to 
$756 million this month. (Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 
18 Jan 94 p 62) 
  President Ramiro De Leon Carpio delivered 3.1 million 
quetzales to the mayors of Chiquimula in his recent working tour 
of that department. De Leon explained that the funds became 
available thanks to his austerity policy. The money will be 
used for public projects in the aforementioned municipalities. 
(Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 24 Jan 94 p 36) 

</TEXT>

