<H3> <TI>   Castro Attends Solidarity Meeting Opening </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2501154394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1502 GMT 
25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2501154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Fourth Latin American and Caribbean Meeting for 
Solidarity, Sovereignty, Self-Determination, and the Lives of 
our People has just been inaugurated at the Palace of 
Conventions in Havana. Commander in Chief Fidel Castro is 
present at the event which is also being attended by more than 
1,000 representatives of the social and people's movements of 
all the countries of the continent and the Antilles. The 
participants at the event will discuss possible alternatives to 
the structural crisis confronted by the region. 

</TEXT>

