<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the eve of his visit to China, Russian Minister 
of Foreign Affairs Andrey Kozyrev has said that normalization of 
relations with China is among the main priorities of Russian 
foreign policy. 
  PRENSA LATINA cited Kozyrev as stating that the development 
of bilateral relations with Beijing is based on the two 
countries' interests and that it strengthens the efforts in the 
quest of international stability. 
  Kosyrev said: Ties between Moscow and Beijing must be based 
on the principles of friendship and cooperation between two 
world powers. According to ITAR-TASS, Kozyrev is making a 
working visit to the Kyrgyz capital before leaving for China. 

