<H3> <TI>   Troops Deployed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2601045194 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 0340 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2601045194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 25 Jan (DPA) -- Managua police are 
preparing to clear the streets of barricades and bonfires that 
are blocking the free flow of privately owned vehicles. The 
obstacles were placed in the streets by demonstrating public 
transportation workers, who are staging a strike to demand a 
reduction in fuel prices. 
  Trucks loaded with troops were deployed following orders 
from 
police headquarters, which received instructions from Government 
Minister Alfredo Mendieta, according to reliable sources. 
  The transportation workers are surrounding those vehicles 
that form roadblocks along several roads. The demonstration 
could become violent after negotiations between government and 
transportation representatives have hit a stalemate. 
  [Paris AFP in Spanish at 0243 GMT on 26 January transmits a 
related 155-word, Managua-datelined report that says union 
leader Gustavo Aguiluz has announced that "two taxi drivers were 
wounded by gunfire and another was beaten." After noting that 
10 demonstrators have been arrested, the AFP report adds that 
Aguiluz "reported police excesses and asked for the Human Rights 
Commission to intervene." The report also says a local radio 
station "reported a shootout between members of different 
cooperative unions, but the station mentioned nothing about 
casualties or the reason for the clash."] 

</TEXT>

