<H3> <TI>   DEA Center for `Intercepting' Communications Discovered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2501180794 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2501180794 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of deputies headed by [Democratic 
Socialism Alternative Deputy] Jerjes Justiniano, [Patriotic 
Accord Deputy] Guido Nayar, and prosecutor Freddy Flores, has 
confirmed the existence of a DEA center for intercepting 
telephone and radio communications of [Santa Cruz] Department 
officials. 
  The delegation visited a property, allegedly owned by the 
DEA, where the existence of the center had been reported, at 
kilometer 11 of the highway to Cotoca. 

