<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indians, Peasants Meet Social Development Secretary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2601021694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2601021694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Indians and peasants of Chiapas have converged on 
San Cristobal de las Casas for the Second Meeting of the State 
Council of Indian and Peasant Organizations [Consejo Estatal de 
Organizaciones Indigenas y Campesinas]. On behalf of dozens of 
Indian and peasant organizations in Chiapas State, Marcelino 
Gomez Nunez, a leader of the National Coordinating Board of the 
Ayala Plan, invited President Carlos Salinas de Gortari to visit 
Ocosingo or San Cristobal de Las Casas as soon as possible. The 
visit would allow the president to get first-hand knowledge of 
the situation from those affected and offer him the opportunity 
to encourage the people to find a solution to the problems 
facing them after the New Year's conflict. 
  The meeting between Indians and peasants and Social 
Development Secretary Carlos Rojas took place at a warehouse 
complex known as El Pajal on the outskirts of San Cristobal, on 
the road to Rancho Nuevo. Eraclio Zepeda and Andres Fabrega, 
members of the National Commission for the Overall Development 
and Social Justice for Indian People were present, as well as 
Rigoberta Menchu, Beatriz Paredes, and Jose Narro Robles. All 
Indian and peasant leaders and representatives repeatedly 
expressed their desire for progress through dialogue. The 
leaders asked Secretary Carlos Rojas to set up a meeting between 
the Indian and peasant organizations and Peace Commissioner 
Manuel Camacho Solis in an attempt to reach agreements that will 
guarantee justice in Chiapas. One of the more important 
proposals made during the meeting was the establishment of a 
produce wholesale program for the conflict area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

