<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner Communique in Response to EZLN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2601032594 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0030 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2601032594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Paloma Boves from the "Vector 21" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Manuel Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in Chiapas, this afternoon sent a communique to 
the Zapatist National Liberation Army [EZLN]. Camacho Solis' 
latest communique was sent in response to the communiques 
released 25 January by the EZLN's Indigenous Revolutionary 
Committee -- communiques in which Commander Marcos demanded that 
the government clearly state the degree to which it recognizes 
the EZLN. Commander Marcos made the demand in an effort to 
assess the value of any guarantees he might receive from the 
government during the dialogue process. 
  In his communique, Camacho Solis says a proposal that will 
be 
released on Thursday will formalize the terms for an honest, 
serious, and responsible meeting. Camacho Solis says the 
groundwork is being laid for a cease-fire, and he assured the 
EZLN that the government is giving humanitarian assistance to 
the communities that require food and health care. Finally, he 
said the communities, society, political parties, and 
institutions are all working to find more respectful ways of 
achieving the pacification demanded in Chiapas by way of a 
national commitment toward democracy, justice, and freedom. 

</TEXT>

